at compositional constraints can be key in determining the\nmass of the disrupted star. The abundance anomalies predicted by these\nsimulations provide a natural explanation for the spectral features and varying\nline strengths observed in tidal disruption events.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 10 Jul 2019 18:00:00 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Tue, 6 Aug 2019 19:25:04 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-10-17"}
